text: Riverside County is one of fifty-eight counties in the U.S. state of California. According to the 2020 census, there were 2,418,185 people living there. It is the 4th-most populous county in California. It's also the 10th- most populous in the whole country. The name came from the city of Riverside, which is its county seat. == References == * Category:1893 establishments in California
title: Riverside County, California
